 of a final class called UnsafeOverrideHarness. If the constructor is package-private, it makes it private and unused, which feels a bit off. Should I perhaps declare it abstract instead to signal that no instances can be created? However, an abstract class still needs a constructor. I see that it’s allowed to have constructors in abstract classes, so that's an option worth keeping in mind.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating accessibility for `UnsafeOverrideHarness`**\\n\\nI’m considering the `UnsafeOverrideHarness`, which seems to be private right now. It might need to be public at the top-level, just so it's accessible where needed. I think I should ensure that it’s properly defined to avoid confusion. I also need to check if any tests are running for this. Finally, I'll aim for a more concise approach before finishing up.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java`\n\nCoverage-focused behavior added:\n- Forces creation of `ClassInjector$UsingReflection$Dispatcher$UsingUnsafeOverride` via a subclass bridge.\n- Exercises:\n  - `make()`\n  - `initialize()` with a `SecurityManager`\n  - `findClass`\n  - `defineClass`\n  - `getDefinedPackage`\n  - `getPackage`\n  - `definePackage`\n- Uses Byte Buddy-generated class bytes and a fresh class loader.\n- Catches Native Image unsupported dynamic class-loading failures with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)` as required.\n\nI did not run or compile the tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02f19d58a0a0b0c40169fa9dc86c0c81a0af8ef5ce1846d3c2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 678, "output": 1716, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWri