8B2nTrl-K7Yumo2k9JafEhxR-XlY4qqEdthVJLu4wX7a8CcCZme_SMsjw7gnbule33LaPge4q-eaTWfKsxo8B63MgE9P2rM8s860oOKwglpFWBCIwx35up-jb6EMkTx_KWZW6j7J3UHB7n44r5LHEwyCuRlnTM2Yu9fypp7n_RyNe8YGuk6zboRKUl19JttsuRFBvEaoTnbw9KijDbzUH_7TLSicRAr5gO-p0aG8y3UNymgndozxG6WF8NwIvh5gmf4V48olIAEnY0QXFiYdoWiZeqShLtOp0OhazM7tFPdZ2_h4cozicR5Fz3QMROy_P_YMTbl1w68doHxuRiygiXjPg0qN5MCCdXHXHir5RRyHjN8zFggcahf8C4B3bTWjnDD50W2-LQeGVZd_qsvqS2WJJK0BzTrlD27NPJRq1w1HGG_8HdgoCaHtZnmWCR5biS5UBsNFzLbG9j0KdSASSgYd8gp-suZtjXDC7Ni2j4mFnFTr1Xl6X9uQedwQUI0o5AHQ3ku2kELSwiXDfrfQnq-xfWqlO2nkJ6NPHZnP3fZmG_3DAdBRt6MS4h7Gs477yJHAJBwKx4zq_wc5wgbkjkayeDhqU3ZAfpBL6cK9zeSrr0sTFgPxyYEjwdxFDTlyOj1XTOoN5BmOw9mhYZRHGQUekN1DrFFw3N0V_gBSy-Ar6LmG-5AsZXYBB4SPgnp1uaMGiyuP4JwkD6oTuSkiTM47tTTa3epEKnuV5xFWuC8S2iOYZ9QGXJFxIojEGtx1osojYBsOjBGuorozLdweBUowVKCi_kpYU6liD0Opho3Oo7bh1J4_IuPxSpGs27xDPNIduGbPbKmX1RWtJMUJWkHnOwc40mfSECXssKUGyOh0jAQOS_h9jhZAPi9gp-OJb1OHiMBaM0b_9ljMmxBGb8OhKdTPLQjnuGXID4Gef1w4w-ptIUP4wOAtfss4AooTPdZSNE_xC-rqk77ec9Bey5xnEK_N0I6Ip_VKN8wzfkko8dCFx9xwbelVBRKL-vu5WfdxzV4bMZxOvzclrDA15m0qlLqlqqL8YcZSONrfJCjNPKrRKTV-fP2Vqljeu-MOX8hHSYswM8YK9Ek=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class creation for testing**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I could create a helper top-level public class for handling tests. I’m thinking about how JUnit scans all compiled test classes and registers selected test classes from a test list. Maybe it only includes JUnit test classes, but I wonder how it would manage nested classes inside a test. This might require some careful planning. Let’s brainstorm how that could work!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Yqk7vwmHclURScLVw8h9196X|fc_02f19d58a0a0b0c40169fa9e1e9b9081a0af6cae225fa10d1b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "\n    private static final class UnsafeOverrideHarness extends ClassInjector.UsingReflection {\n        UnsafeOverrideHarness(ClassLoader classLoader) {\n            super(classLoader);\n        }\n\n        static DispatcherHarness createDispatcher() throws Exception {\n            Dispatcher.Initializable initializable = ExposedUsingUnsafeOverride.makeDispatcher();\n            assertThat(initializable.isAvailable()).isTrue();\n            return new DispatcherHarness(initializable.initialize());\n        }\n\n        private static final class DispatcherHarness {\n            private final Dispatcher dispatcher;\n\n            private DispatcherHarness(Dispatcher dispatcher) {\n                this.dispatcher = dispatcher;\n            }\n\n            Class<?> findClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String className) {\n                return dispatcher.findClass(classLoader, className);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> defineClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String className, byte[] binaryRepresentation) {\n                return dispatcher.defineClass(classLoader, className, binaryRepresentation,\n                        getClass().getProtectionDomain());\n            }\n\n            Package getDefinedPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String packageName) {\n                return dispatcher.getDefinedPackage(classLoader, packageName);\n            }\n\n            Package getPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String packageName) {\n                return dispatcher.getPackage(classLoader, packageName);\n            }\n\n            Package definePackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String packageName, String specificationTitle,\n                    String specificationVersion, String specificationVendor, String implementationTitle,\n                    String implementationVersion, String implementationVendor, URL sealBase) {\n                return dispatcher.definePackage(classLoader, packageName, specificationTitle, specificationVersion,\n                        specificationVendor, implementationTitle, implementationVersion, implementationVendor, sealBase);\n            }\n        }\n\n        private abstract static class ExposedUsingUnsafeOverride extends Dispatcher.UsingUnsafeOverride {\n            ExposedUsingUnsafeOverride(Method findLoadedClass, Method defineClass, Method getDefinedPackage,\n                    Method getPackage, Method definePackage) {\n                super(findLoadedClass, defineClass, getDefinedPackage, getPackage, definePackage);\n            }\n\n            static Dispatcher.Initializable makeDispatcher() throws Exception {\n                return make();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "}\n\nfinal class UnsafeOverrideHarness extends ClassInjector.UsingReflection {\n    UnsafeOverrideHarness(ClassLoader classLoader) {\n        super(classLoader);\n    }\n\n    static DispatcherHarness createDispatcher() throws Exception {\n        Dispatcher.Initializable initializable = ExposedUsingUnsafeOverride.makeDispatcher();\n        assertThat(initializable.isAvailable()).isTrue();\n        return new DispatcherHarness(initializable.initialize());\n    }\n\n    static final class DispatcherHarness {\n        private final Dispatcher dispatcher;\n\n        private DispatcherHarness(Dispatcher dispatcher) {\n            this.dispatcher = dispatcher;\n        }\n\n        Class<?> findClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String className) {\n            return dispatcher.findClass(classLoader, className);\n        }\n\n        Class<?> defineClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String className, byte[] binaryRepresentation) {\n            return dispatcher.defineClass(classLoader, className, binaryRepresentation,\n                    getClass().getProtectionDomain());\n        }\n\n        Package getDefinedPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String packageName) {\n            return dispatcher.getDefinedPackage(classLoader, packageName);\n        }\n\n        Package getPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String packageName) {\n   